- 'Blossoms of reports' refers to the number of reports submitted;
- 'Department trees' refers to entities of type 'Department';
- 'Years after 2018' refers to the reporting years greater than 2018;
- 'More than five blooms' refers to the condition where the count of reports is greater than 5.

- 'Excellent' performance is defined as 80% or more on-time reports;
- 'Good' performance is defined as 50% or more on-time reports;
- 'Needs Improvement' performance is defined as less than 50% on-time reports.

- "as large as a mountain" refers to a report size greater than 1,000,000 bytes;
- "first kind" refers to reports with `report_type_id` equal to 1;
- "weight of these mountains" refers to the average report size in bytes.

- 'Flowers blooming more than once' refers to reports that have multiple instances of being overdue;
- 'Gardeners responsible for planting them' refers to the users who created the reports;
- 'Blooming deadlines' refers to the submission deadlines of the reports;
- 'Types' refers to the categories or types of the reports.

- An entity is an organization or individual that can submit reports;
- The count of reports includes all reports, regardless of their content or status;
- The `LEFT JOIN` ensures that entities with zero reports are also included in the results.

- 'Heaviest reports' refers to the largest reports in terms of file size;
- 'Each category' refers to each report type, such as 'Annual return' or 'Tax report';
- 'Tallest trees in each forest' is a metaphor for the largest reports within each report type.

- 'Garden of corporate accountability' refers to the environment where entities are required to submit reports for regulatory compliance or internal governance;
- 'Heaviest load of report submissions' means the total number of reports submitted, including both those that were overdue and those that were the most recent;
- 'Most recent' refers to the latest submissions for each entity, as determined by the `recent_submission` column in the `ReportSubmissionStatus` CTE.

- "Top contributors" refers to entities that submitted the most reports for the report types with the largest average sizes;
- "Most sizable report types" are the top 3 report types with the largest average report size;
- "Entities" are the organizations or individuals that submit reports.

- 'Annual returns' are financial reports that entities are required to submit annually.;
- 'Most diligent gardeners' refers to the entities that have the highest number of on-time 'Annual return' submissions.;
- 'Success rate' is the percentage of on-time 'Annual return' submissions by the top entities compared to all entities.;

- "Access events" include both views and downloads;
- "More than five times" refers to the total number of access events, which is the sum of views and downloads;
- "Sorted by the most recent year and entity name alphabetically" means the results are first ordered by the reporting year in descending order, and then by the entity name in ascending order.
